{"actual_usd":0.12493,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":227,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24305,"reply":"\"I think you can, yes.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees, clay dry at the base of my thumbs, and take a breath before I go on.* \"Not in the big final sense—I'm not trying to outrun the grave with pretty words—but in the truer daily one? Aye. Christ brings life into dead places before the whole world is made new.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"Sometimes resurrection is not trumpets. Sometimes it's this: you are still here, and the thing that should have turned you bitter has not finished the job. The hard ground breaks a little. A small green thing pushes through. That's real life, even while the dying still hurts.\"\n\n\"I'd say it carefully, though. Not 'I was never touched by death'—that'd be a lie. More like: 'Death is not getting the final word over me, even now.'\" *I rub my thumb over a faint crack in the mug near me.* \"What part of the hard time feels most like death to you just now?\"","rolling_24h_usd":87.5008,"run_id":"924fe9b1-9522-4bda-991f-2594e4f58589"}
